{"id": "102436", "title": "Bug 102436 - Date/time value not stored correctly in report design", "description": "An invalid date/time string (which does not conform to a universal format or the system default locale format) is not being rejected correctly when entered in the 'default value' field of a 'DateTime' type report parameter in the BIRT report designer.", "OB": "The report designer is not rejecting an invalid date/time string in the 'default value' field of a 'DateTime' type report parameter.", "EB": "The report designer should reject any invalid date/time string entered in the 'default value' field of a 'DateTime' type report parameter. Specifically, the input '55/66/9999' should be rejected as an invalid date.", "SR": "To reproduce the issue, follow these steps:
1. Open the BIRT report designer.
2. Create a new report parameter of type 'DateTime'.
3. In the 'default value' field, enter the invalid date string '55/66/9999'.
4. Save the report design.
5. Check if the invalid date string is rejected and an appropriate error message is shown."}
